I was 16 years old when I was asked to have spinal fusion surgery. Without a doubt, I automatically said yes. The doctor said if I did not it would affect my breathing and the curve would get even worst as I age. I am glad I made that decision to have the surgery. My mother asked if I wanted time to think about it and I didn't want to. Anyone with my condition knows the looks and stares we get because of our deep scars. It doesn't make us any different than you. When people ask why I have the scar, they cringe and make facial expressions. Next time someone tells you about their scar story do not be a jerk and cringe. Do you ever think how it makes the other person feel? We already have low self esteem and constant pain. It sucks being limited in what we do... Next time you make a rude remark or body expression keep it to yourself. Here's another video, this time cutting the tails of a houndstooth dovetail in hard maple...a little slower going then my walnut video! My preferred saw is my 14" Disston tenon rip saw. It cuts great in the thick hard maple. I am cutting the waste out with the coping saw above the line and then I'll trim down to the line with a chisel. I'll be bringing this dovetailed corner along with me on the plane to  Handworks this weekend. I'll be doing the touristy thing on Friday and then I'll be set up next to @Benchcrafted on Saturday, doing some little demos on inlay and dovetails, as well as talking about my benches and furniture. I'm looking forward to seeing old friends and meeting new ones!!
